cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of video streaming over heterogeneous wireless networks using multipath transfer. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video streaming and optimizing the video quality, which is a key aspect of multimedia research. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses utility maximization theory to derive the solution for minimizing end-to-end video distortion. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper proposes a solution that involves dynamically picking appropriate access networks and assigning transmission rates, which can be seen as a multi-agent system. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses H.264 video streaming, which is a widely used video compression standard in computer vision and pattern recognition research.
